messages.message:
Folks, I started getting random mypy error when running `make test` in some python services, e.g.
```xicheng@C02DV9T6MD6R api-server-apps % make clean build test
...
instabase/handler/api/v1/dataset.py:2093: error: Need type annotation for 'classes_to_add'```
Anyone runs into similar problem? If so, why was this not caught during pre-merge/post-merge?
The mypy version on my mac matches this doc (https://docs.google.com/document/d/1yQOCxOISV_ukUxXdPJDoN-rERtOhdVRe7zv1swF1igw/edit#):
```mypy==0.701
mypy-extensions==0.4.3```
